{"questionId":"9084422","questionHtml":"<p>Planets X and Y orbit the same star.</p>\n<p>The average distance between planet X and the star is five times greater than the average&nbsp;distance between planet Y and the star.</p>\n<p>What is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>orbital</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>period</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>of</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>planet</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>orbital</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>period</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>of</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>planet</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mroot><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></mroot></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mroot><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>3</mn></mroot></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9084422","referenceCode":"SPM.1A.HL.TZ0.28","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Planets X and Y orbit the same star. The average distance between planet X and the star is five times greater than the average distance between planet Y and the star. What is orbit","paper":"1A","level":"HL","questionNumber":"28","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["A. Space, time and motion","D. Fields","D. Fields","D.1 Gravitational fields","A. Space, time and motion","A.2 Forces and momentum"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}